1 (g) Gender identity. The State Registrar may correct or amend a death
2 certificate to reflect the deceased person’s gender identity at the time of death,
3 upon application by:
4 (1) the certifying licensed health care professional, medical examiner,
5 hospital, or nursing home; or
6 (2) the spouse, child, grandchild, parent, sibling, grandparent, or
7 guardian of the deceased person.
8 (h) Rules. Pursuant to 3 V.S.A. chapter 25, the Department shall adopt
9 rules as necessary for the purposes of implementing, administering, or
10 enforcing the correction or amendment of death certificates pursuant to
11 subsection (g) of this section. The rules adopted pursuant to this subsection
12 shall include:
13 (1) a list of the documents that may be accepted as prima facie evidence
14 of the deceased person’s gender identity, including any relevant information
15 contained in an advanced directive;
16 (2) the forms and affidavits that shall be used to attest to the deceased
17 person’s identity at the time of death; and
18 (3) procedures for an individual to file a predesignation of their gender
19 identity, which may be used by the State Registrar to render a final decision
20 concerning the correction or amendment of a death certificate.
