1 Sec. 2. DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH; RULEMAKING; LEGISLATIVE
2 INTENT
3 It is the intent of the General Assembly that the Department of Health,
4 exercising rulemaking authority pursuant to this act, shall adopt a
5 comprehensive procedure for a health care professional or surviving family
6 member to attest to the gender identity of a deceased person. The procedure
7 shall ensure that any conflicting requests for the correction or amendment of
8 the gender identity on a death certificate are resolved through the consideration
9 and review of appropriate evidence.
10 Sec. 3. EFFECTIVE DATE
11 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
